expression: "loom_help(&[\"check\"])"
---
Deterministic audits — `[verify]` scripts, style linters, and `<audit>` sub-audits

Usage: loom check [OPTIONS] [AUDIT]

Arguments:
  [AUDIT]  Sub-audit to run (`criteria`, `matrix`, `surface`); omit to run the full deterministic pass [possible values: criteria, matrix, surface]

Options:
  -s, --spec <LABEL>      Spec label override (defaults to `current_spec`)
  -w, --workspace <PATH>  Workspace root. Defaults to the current working directory
  -A, --agent <BACKEND>   Override the agent backend for this invocation [possible values: claude, pi]
  -b, --bead <ID>         Restrict the audit scope to one bead
      --diff <RANGE>      Restrict the audit scope to a git diff range
      --tree              Audit the entire spec tree × implementation
      --strict            Promote warning-severity findings (e.g. orphan stubs) to errors. Applies to `loom check criteria`
      --no-run            Skip executing live verifiers — only run structural checks (stubbed, missing-dispatcher, orphan, masquerade). Applies to `loom check criteria` and is intended for the pre-commit hook path where the full live audit is too slow
  -h, --help              Print help
